# 1993 Guinean presidential election

Presidential elections were held in Guinea on 19 December 1993. They were the first since the country returned to multi-party politics in 1990, and the first to feature more than one candidate. The result was a victory for Lansana Cont√© of the Unity and Progress Party, who received 52% of the vote. Voter turnout was 78%.
